msgid ""
"The mechanism for name resolution in Linux is modular and can use various "
"sources of information declared in the <filename>/etc/nsswitch.conf</"
"filename> file. The entry that involves host name resolution is "
"<literal>hosts</literal>. By default, it contains <literal>files dns</"
"literal>, which means that the system consults the <filename>/etc/hosts</"
"filename> file first, then DNS servers. NIS/NIS+ or LDAP servers are other "
"possible sources."
msgstr ""
