#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The tilde is often used to indicate the directory to which the environment "
"variable, <varname>HOME</varname>, points (being the user's home directory, "
"such as <filename>/home/rhertzog/</filename>). Command interpreters "
"automatically make the substitution: <filename>~/hello.txt</filename> "
"becomes <filename>/home/rhertzog/hello.txt</filename>."
